Class DatabaseMetaData

  • java.lang.Object
    • curam.util.dataaccess.DatabaseMetaData

  • public class DatabaseMetaData
extends java.lang.Object
    DatabaseMetaData is used to construct and transfer the Database related meta-data configuration.

        Create a new data meta data object. This overload of the function is used for read and remove operations.
        Parameters:
        rsltClass - The class of object returned by this data access.
        arg1 - The class of the first argument that will be passed to "execute()" calls on the data access object.
        arg2 - The class of the second argument that will be passed to "execute()" calls on the data access object.
        stereotype - The stereotype of the data access pattern to be used.
        table - The database table that will be access by the operation.
        opName - The name of the method on the entity which initiated the data access.
        performAuditing - Whether the database updates done by this operation should be recorded on an audit trail.
        auditMappingsHelper - The audit mapping helper for this operation, or null if this operation does not write to audit mapping fields.
        useOptimisticLocking - Whether an update operation should use the optimistic locking pattern.

        Create a new data meta data object. This overload of the functions is used only for insert operations using the "Auto ID" and the "Last Updated Field" patterns.
        Parameters:
        rsltClass - The class of object returned by this data access.
        arg1 - The class of the first argument that will be passed to "execute()" calls on the data access object.
        arg2 - The class of the second argument that will be passed to "execute()" calls on the data access object.
        stereotype - The stereotype of the data access pattern to be used.
        table - The database table that will be access by the operation.
        opName - The name of the method on the entity which initiated the data access.
        performAuditing - Whether the database updates done by this operation should be recorded on an audit trail.
        auditMappingsHelper - The audit mapping helper for this operation, or null if this operation does not write to audit mapping fields.
        useOptimisticLocking - Whether an update operation should use the optimistic locking pattern.
        autoID - The name of a database column that should be automatically set to a new unique id.
        autoIDKey - The name of the unique id key set from which the new unique ID should be selected.
        useLastUpdatedField - Whether an insert or update operation should use the last updated field pattern.
